      "code": "# define normalization helpers\nimport unicodedata, re\n\narabic_diacritics = re.compile(r'[\\u0610-\\u061A\\u064B-\\u065F\\u0670\\u06D6-\\u06ED]')\ndef normalize_ar(text):\n    if text is None:\n        return \"\"\n    # remove tatweel\n    t = re.sub(r'ـ', '', text)\n    # remove diacritics\n    t = arabic_diacritics.sub('', t)\n    # unify hamza forms: إ أ آ ؤ ئ -> ا ? But rule says unify hamza; We'll map to bare alef forms maybe.\n    t = t.replace('أ','ا').replace('إ','ا').replace('آ','ا').replace('ؤ','و').replace('ئ','ي').replace('ى','ي')\n    # remove punctuation and non letters/digits\n    t = re.sub(r'[^\\w\\s]', ' ', t)\n    # collapse spaces and lowercase (though Arabic has no lowercase)\n    t = re.sub(r'\\s+',' ', t).strip()\n    return t\n\n# find entries with iblis\ncandidates=[]\nfor entry in data:\n    txt=entry.get('ayah_text','')\n    if 'إبليس' in txt or 'ابليس' in txt or 'إِبْلِيس' in txt:\n        candidates.append(entry)\nlen(candidates)\n",
